<p>Monday 16th April 1917<br/>Bapaume<br/>Grooming in the morning and had just started cleaning harness about 2.30pm when we had to leave the lines as a few of Fritz shells landed near the mules, so we ran back and took them about a mile to a flank, as our camp was in the line of fire. Another shell landed about 50 feet away from the wagons loaded with ammunition, but did not damage it. Returned to camp in about an hour and a half, put rugs on mules and fixed up new lines, about a mile away. As it was too late to shift out huts we slept in them that</p>
